# Trial INDEX

Retired trial index template. Use `assets/shared/INDEX.md.template` and
`scripts/new_trial.py` for new projects.

## Entries

| trial_id | workstream label | linked claim / objective | state row updated | notebook status | state update / result summary |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|

## Notebook-status legend (per notebook)

- `planned`: accepted through the entry gate, notebook not created
- `in-progress`: notebook created, trial not yet interpreted
- `done`: observation, interpretation, and research-state update are recorded
- `parked`: blocked on upstream dependency
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing; reason recorded in decisions.md

A notebook is `done` only when it has been interpreted and the relevant state
document, report package, or decision log has cited it. A metric without
interpretation is still unfinished.

## Order

Sequential numbering is for reviewability. Dependencies and blocking state rows
take precedence over chronology when deciding what to run next.
